SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 900
By Walley
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Barry Crews upon
being named the 2025 Master Logger of the
Year by the Tennessee Forestry Association.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we should salute those citizens who, through their
extraordinary efforts, have distinguished themselves as community leaders of whom we can all
be proud; and
WHEREAS, one such noteworthy individual is Barry Crews of Waynesboro, who was
selected as the 2025 Master Logger of the Year by the Tennessee Forestry Association; and
WHEREAS, a Tennessee Master Logger since 2000, Barry Crews is the owner of Crews
Logging and Sawmill in Waynesboro; his family has been in the logging and sawmill business
since 1950, and he took ownership of the family operation in 1986; and
WHEREAS, leaders in the logging and forest-products industry in Tennessee, Mr. Crews
and his family advocate for small business success, best management conservation practices,
and safety in the mill, on the roadway, and in the woods; and
WHEREAS, the family business includes Mr. Crews's three sons, Blake, Blaine, and
Lance, who work with their father in the logging and sawmill operation, as well as two brothers-
in-law and two nephews, who work in the woods with the logging crew and in the sawmill; and
WHEREAS, Barry Crews's brother, Danny Crews, joined the business as a partner
several years after Barry took control of the family business; Danny Crews took his much-
deserved retirement from the company in 2024; and
WHEREAS, thanks to Mr. Crews's logging and mill operations, numerous jobs have
been created; the company itself now employs approximately forty-seven individuals across
Wayne and Lawrence counties; and
SJR0900
014902
- 1 -

WHEREAS, the economy of rural southern Middle Tennessee has benefited from Barry
Crews's lifetime commitment to sustaining the workforce and ensuring healthy forests for our
future generations; and
WHEREAS, an active part of his community, Mr. Crews is a key supporter for area
school and community athletics and other activities. His family has annually provided donations
to help St. Jude and Log a Load for Kids, a fundraising initiative that supports children's
hospitals; and
WHEREAS, Barry Crews epitomizes the spirit and commitment that are characteristic of
a true Tennessean; and
WHEREAS, we find it appropriate to acknowledge and applaud Mr. Crews for his
dedication to the State of Tennessee and its citizens; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Barry Crews upon being
named the 2025 Master Logger of the Year by the Tennessee Forestry Association and extend
to him our best wishes for success in all his future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
